---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="DeDuper Privacy Policy"
  description="DeDuper does not collect, sell, or share your data. Your photos never leave your device — all processing is on-device, with no network access, accounts, or tracking."
>
  <main>

    <!-- ─── Hero ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="section privacy-hero reveal">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="crumb mono muted">
          <a href="/deduper">DeDuper</a> <span aria-hidden="true">/</span> Privacy
        </div>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="meta mono muted">Effective May 29, 2026 &nbsp;·&nbsp; App version 1.0 and later</p>

        <div class="summary-box card">
          <p>
            <strong>Short version:</strong> DeDuper does not collect, sell, or share your
            personal data. Your photos <strong>never leave your device — period.</strong>
            All processing happens locally; the app makes no network requests at all.
            DeDuper is free, requires no account, and includes no analytics or tracking of any kind.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ─── Policy ────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="section reveal">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="policy">

          <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
          <p>
            DeDuper is developed and published by Siddharth Bobba
            (<a class="inline-link" href="mailto:siddharthdbobba@gmail.com">siddharthdbobba@gmail.com</a>).
            "We", "our", and "us" refer to this individual developer. "You" means anyone who installs
            or uses DeDuper on macOS or iOS.
          </p>

          <h2>2. What DeDuper Does</h2>
          <p>
            DeDuper is a duplicate photo cleaner. It scans your Photos library (or a folder you select),
            groups visually similar or time-adjacent photos, scores them automatically, and lets you delete
            the lower-quality copies. All scanning, grouping, and scoring happens entirely on your device
            using Apple system frameworks.
          </p>

          <h2>3. Data We Do Not Collect</h2>
          <p>We do not collect, store, transmit, or process any of the following:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Your photos, videos, or any media files</li>
            <li>Your name, email address, or any contact information</li>
            <li>Your Apple ID or any account credentials</li>
            <li>Your location</li>
            <li>Device identifiers or advertising IDs</li>
            <li>Crash reports or usage analytics</li>
            <li>Any behavioral or diagnostic telemetry</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            DeDuper contains <strong>no analytics SDKs, no crash-reporting services, and no third-party
            tracking libraries</strong> of any kind.
          </p>

          <h2>4. Photo Library Access</h2>
          <p>
            DeDuper requests access to your Photos library solely to scan for duplicate and similar photos.
            This access is handled entirely by Apple's <strong>Photos framework</strong> on your device.
            The app reads photo metadata (timestamps, dimensions, file size) and generates small perceptual
            hashes locally to compare images. No photo data is ever uploaded, transmitted, or stored outside
            your device as part of the scanning process.
          </p>
          <p>
            On macOS, you may also grant DeDuper access to a specific folder on your file system. Files in
            that folder are read locally and never transmitted.
          </p>
          <p>
            You can revoke photo library access at any time in
            <span class="mono">System Settings → Privacy &amp; Security → Photos</span> (macOS) or
            <span class="mono">Settings → Privacy &amp; Security → Photos</span> (iOS).
          </p>

          <h2>5. On-Device Close-Call Resolution</h2>
          <p>
            When two photos in a group score very closely, DeDuper uses Apple's on-device
            <strong>Vision framework</strong> to break the tie — analyzing face sharpness, whether eyes are
            open, and overall image aesthetics — and shows a short "Why this one?" explanation. This analysis
            runs <strong>entirely on your device</strong>. No photo, hash, or analysis result is ever
            transmitted anywhere. There is no AI assistant, cloud service, or external API involved.
          </p>

          <h2>6. No Network Access</h2>
          <p>
            DeDuper makes <strong>no network requests of any kind</strong>. It has no servers, no accounts,
            no API integrations, and no telemetry. The app functions identically with networking fully
            disabled. (On macOS, the app does not even request the network entitlement.)
          </p>

          <h2>7. Free App — No In-App Purchases</h2>
          <p>
            DeDuper is free. There are no in-app purchases, subscriptions, premium tiers, or paid features.
            The app collects no payment information because there is nothing to buy.
          </p>

          <h2>8. Local Storage</h2>
          <p>DeDuper stores the following data <strong>only on your device</strong>:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>App preferences</strong> (scan sensitivity, time window, protected albums, etc.) —
              stored in <span class="mono">UserDefaults</span>, on-device only, never synced to iCloud.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Audit log</strong> — a local CSV record of photos you have deleted using DeDuper.
              Stored in the app's sandboxed container. Never transmitted. You can export or review this log
              at any time from Settings → Audit Log, and it is removed when you uninstall the app.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>No data is stored in iCloud, synced across devices, or accessible to the developer.</p>

          <h2>9. No Advertising or Third-Party SDKs</h2>
          <p>
            DeDuper contains no advertising, no advertising identifiers, and no third-party SDKs of any kind.
            The app makes no external network contact whatsoever.
          </p>

          <h2>10. Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            DeDuper is rated 4+ and is suitable for all ages. Because we do not collect any personal data
            from any user, no special provisions for users under 13 (COPPA) or under 16 (GDPR) are required
            beyond the general protections described in this policy.
          </p>

          <h2>11. Data Retention and Deletion</h2>
          <p>
            We do not retain any data about you because we do not collect any. All app data (preferences,
            audit log) is stored locally on your device and is deleted automatically when you uninstall DeDuper.
          </p>

          <h2>12. Your Rights</h2>
          <p>
            Because we collect no personal data, there is nothing for us to provide, correct, or delete on
            our end. If you have questions about data processed by Apple (the Photos framework), please consult
            Apple's privacy policy. If you have any concerns about DeDuper specifically, please contact us at
            the address below.
          </p>

          <h2>13. Security</h2>
          <p>
            DeDuper operates within Apple's strict app-sandbox model, which limits its access to only the
            resources you explicitly grant. Because the app performs all work on-device and makes no network
            requests, your photos are never exposed to any network or third party.
          </p>

          <h2>14. Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p>
            If we make material changes to this policy, we will update the effective date at the top of this
            page and, where possible, notify users through an app update. Continued use of DeDuper after changes
            are posted constitutes acceptance of the revised policy. We encourage you to review this page periodically.
          </p>

          <h2>15. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this privacy policy or DeDuper's data
            practices, please contact:
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Siddharth Bobba</strong><br />
            <a class="inline-link" href="mailto:siddharthdbobba@gmail.com">siddharthdbobba@gmail.com</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ─── Back ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="section back-section">
      <div class="container" style="text-align: center;">
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/deduper">← Back to DeDuper</a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  .privacy-hero { padding-top: 72px; padding-bottom: 24px; }
  .crumb        { margin-bottom: 20px; font-size: 0.85rem; }
  .crumb a      { color: var(--muted); transition: color 0.15s; }
  .crumb a:hover { color: var(--accent); }
  .meta         { margin-top: 12px; font-size: 0.82rem; }

  .summary-box {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin-top: 28px;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    border-radius: 0 var(--radius) var(--radius) 0;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .inline-link { color: var(--accent); }
  .inline-link:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

  .policy { max-width: 720px; }
  .policy h2 {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: 36px;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    padding-bottom: 6px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .policy p  { font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .policy ul { margin: 10px 0 14px 22px; }
  .policy li { font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 6px; }

  .back-section { padding-top: 24px; padding-bottom: 48px; }

  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .privacy-hero { padding-top: 48px; }
  }
</style>
